Doctor chosen to
replace Detre in
health sciences and
medical school

Dr. Arthur S. Levine will replace
Dr. Thomas Detre as senior vice chan-
cellor for health sciences after Detre’s
retirement on November 1.

Levine, 61, is scientiﬁc director of
the National Institute of Child Health
and Human Development, a division of
the National Institutes of Health.

He was chosen out of 181 appli-
cants to head the health sciences depart-
ment and medical school after a six-year
search by University officials.

Levine will oversee the six health
sciences schools, which employ 1,880
full- and part-time faculty, have 1,400
staff members and an enrollment of
3,600 students.

At the National Institutes of Health,
Levine leads a research division that is
one of the world’s leading centers for
developmental, molecular, cellular and
structural biology, neuroscience and
clinical research.

